Truly from the bottom of my heart, thank you SO MUCH for the support you’ve shown my business. 🥹 I’ve been a full time photographer since 2014 and it’s all because of every one of you! I strive to never take that for granted! 🙏🏻

I’ve seen so many parts of the world just by simply operating a camera, and that is just the coolest thing. If you would have told younger me that I would currently be sitting in an airport ready to travel to Arizona to photograph a wedding, she wouldn’t have believed you. I’m just so so so grateful. 🫶

This year I was able to add two amazing associate photographers, Matti and Grace, who allow me to be able to serve even more amazing couples, and I’m excited to see how that continues to grow. 🤍

Cheers to 2023, all the amazing people I’ll get to work with, and what the future holds for this business I’m thankful to call my own, all because of you. ✨

In honor of Zealand’s due date today, I thought I’d share some of our maternity photos since I didn’t get the chance to before he came. 😅 It’s hard to believe we’ve gotten to know him outside of the womb for 4.5 weeks already.  I’m so tired these days, and some days are emotionally taxing, but I’m continually reminded how fast these days go.  Feeling so thankful for the unique family story the Lord has given us. 🤍

Happy father’s day to our favorite guy.  You are a picture of someone we can always count on - faithful in all you do.  You are the best at making forts and brownies, affectionately known as “daddy-fix-it”, you give a mean hip squeeze during laboring times (🤪), and you’re the king of all lawn care (no one can wear a new balance 608 like you can). I’ve loved reliving the newborn season with you and watching how well you care for our kids.  You never complain about changing a diaper, and always joyfully ask what you can help with. This past year you’ve shown me such tenderness, protection, and love as we worked on growing our family. I pray our kiddos reflect many of your amazing qualities you display to us. I cannot imagine life without you, and I’m forever grateful to call you the father of our children. 🩵
The amount of excitement I have for our Grace getting ready to marry Timothy is just too much. They are simply the best. 💖

caught red handed 💄

This past year, the Lord has been so kind to me. Through mountaintops and valleys, I had a faith-filled husband holding my hand in each moment. I witnessed my daughter grow not only physically, but to love the Lord with her heart and want to follow him. Nearly a year ago, I saw a positive pregnancy test before my eyes, something I made peace never seeing in my life. Funny how years later, the Lord can choose to open a closed door you thought was sealed shut. Only God. This past year I also experienced one of the most beautiful mountaintop experiences, bringing our son into the world. Through it all, God is tender and kind in His love for me. He knows me and cares for me, and each of us, personally. How sweet a gift.

Cheers to another year of life, and trusting God through whatever may come my way. 🕊️🫶

HAPPY NEW YEAR 🪩💓

Did you stay in or go out last night to celebrate?!

A favorite image from each of my weddings this year - you can tell I am into black and white photographs these days 🤩🤍🖤

I’m truly so grateful to have gotten to know and photograph each one of my couples this past year. It’s a true honor to be a fly on the wall on your wedding day, noticing and capturing moments you might not even see with your own eyes. I truly love it and am so happy to call this my career for over a decade. 🥹 Cheers to 2024 and all the amazing wedding days it holds! 🪩❤️‍🔥

ITS 2024, seniors!! 🪩

Excited to announce my class of 2025 senior session dates at the end of this month ❤️‍🔥 This year I had so many amazing seniors, including Claire. 🫶 Can’t wait to see what this summer brings 🤩

Just blogged a favorite wedding of my associate Emma’s and just so obsessed with everything about it!! @oftheearthweddings knocked it out of the park with their florals. 🤩 I’m so excited to see how Emma captures Maddie’s sister Claire’s wedding this summer 🤩

Maddie and Garrett shared the kindest words with us after their wedding day: 

“Emma’s ability to capture the essence of our relationship in both our engagement shoot and throughout our wedding was nothing short of extraordinary. Each photo tells a story, and looking through our wedding album feels like reliving the most magical day of our lives. The candid shots are filled with genuine laughter, tears of joy, and the warmth of loved ones. The team managed to capture not only visual elements, but also the emotions, allowing us to truly treasure the memories for a lifetime, creating a collection of photos that exceeded our wildest expectations.“

Find inspiration from the rest of their wedding by checking it out on the blog! Link in bio ❤️‍🔥

Dreaming of warmer days today as I watch the snow fall outside my window. ❄️ Elise and Tennyson are my next wedding of 2024 and I couldn’t be more excited 🤩🥳 Bring on the spring weddings! 

I’m currently booking the rest of my 2024 and into 2025, so if you’re engaged, reach out and let’s chat about adding your special day to my calendar 🪩⚡️
